00:10:00.110 --> 00:10:02.100 align:middle line:90%
and claim our own divinity.

00:10:02.100 --> 00:10:04.600 align:middle line:84%
And resurrect the
mystical practices

00:10:04.600 --> 00:10:06.137 align:middle line:90%
that will help us do that.

00:10:06.137 --> 00:10:06.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:10:06.720 --> 00:10:09.080 align:middle line:84%
I felt very
similarly as a child.

00:10:09.080 --> 00:10:12.049 align:middle line:84%
I was raised as a
Christian, a rather dour--

00:10:12.049 --> 00:10:13.423 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: What
kind of Christian?

00:10:13.423 --> 00:10:14.110 align:middle line:90%
V Missouri Synod Lutheran.

00:10:14.110 --> 00:10:15.730 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Oh, my God,
that's very dour.

00:10:15.730 --> 00:10:16.938 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: As dour as it gets.

00:10:16.938 --> 00:10:18.660 align:middle line:90%
As dry as it gets.

00:10:18.660 --> 00:10:21.489 align:middle line:84%
And very dogmatic,
as a matter of fact.

00:10:21.489 --> 00:10:22.780 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Only faith saves you.

00:10:22.780 --> 00:10:23.370 align:middle line:90%
No works do.

00:10:23.370 --> 00:10:23.870 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:10:23.870 --> 00:10:24.876 align:middle line:90%
Oh, Lord, yes.

00:10:24.876 --> 00:10:26.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like I said, it's like
Catholicism without the fun.

00:10:26.160 --> 00:10:26.743 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Yes.

00:10:26.743 --> 00:10:28.890 align:middle line:84%
If you're going to
have a corrupt church,

00:10:28.890 --> 00:10:33.230 align:middle line:84%
have the drag queens, have the
incense, have the whole thing.

00:10:33.230 --> 00:10:34.430 align:middle line:90%
Don't go for drab.

00:10:34.430 --> 00:10:34.680 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Something that
has a lot of juicy stuff.

00:10:34.680 --> 00:10:34.880 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:10:34.880 --> 00:10:36.060 align:middle line:90%
This was as drab as it gets.

00:10:36.060 --> 00:10:40.270 align:middle line:84%
But the dogma of it was such
that, even by the age of five,

00:10:40.270 --> 00:10:42.730 align:middle line:84%
when it was explained
to me-- I remember

00:10:42.730 --> 00:10:45.770 align:middle line:84%
asking my mother at
that time, but Mom,

00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:49.250 align:middle line:84%
what happens to a baby in
China that never had a chance

00:10:49.250 --> 00:10:50.960 align:middle line:84%
to learn about
Jesus, and then dies?

00:10:50.960 --> 00:10:52.501 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Oh, this
is such craziness.

00:10:52.501 --> 00:10:54.857 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And she said,
well, no one said it's fair.

00:10:54.857 --> 00:10:56.190 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: No one says it's fair?

00:10:56.190 --> 00:10:56.790 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:10:56.790 --> 00:10:58.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No one says it's fair.

00:10:58.650 --> 00:11:00.735 align:middle line:84%
And that became a real
disconnect in my psyche.

00:11:00.735 --> 00:11:02.360 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Well, it's
rubbish, isn't it?

00:11:02.360 --> 00:11:02.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is.

00:11:02.810 --> 00:11:04.351 align:middle line:84%
Because there's
something else imbued

00:11:04.351 --> 00:11:06.350 align:middle line:84%
in any religion
of a larger nature

00:11:06.350 --> 00:11:09.040 align:middle line:84%
that you're absorbing
almost on a cellular level.

00:11:09.040 --> 00:11:12.990 align:middle line:84%
And then to have your mind
confused to that degree

00:11:12.990 --> 00:11:15.957 align:middle line:84%
creates, usually, a
falling away of some type.

00:11:15.957 --> 00:11:18.040 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Well it creates
a kind of schizophrenia,

00:11:18.040 --> 00:11:18.880 align:middle line:90%
let's face it.

00:11:18.880 --> 00:11:22.520 align:middle line:84%
Look, Jesus didn't come
to form a religion.

00:11:22.520 --> 00:11:24.760 align:middle line:90%
We've had enough religions.

00:11:24.760 --> 00:11:27.640 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't into the
business of being adored.

00:11:27.640 --> 00:11:31.530 align:middle line:84%
He came to show a
revolutionary path that

00:11:31.530 --> 00:11:34.200 align:middle line:84%
could lead you to be an
instrument of love and justice

00:11:34.200 --> 00:11:37.300 align:middle line:84%
in action, which is
much, much greater

00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:39.220 align:middle line:90%
than finding a religion.

00:11:39.220 --> 00:11:41.990 align:middle line:84%
Many lunatics have
founded a religion.

00:11:41.990 --> 00:11:44.190 align:middle line:84%
Very few have given
the path to humanity

00:11:44.190 --> 00:11:48.250 align:middle line:84%
of evolutionary transfiguration,
which is what he did.

00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:51.290 align:middle line:84%
Can you really
believe that a being

00:11:51.290 --> 00:11:54.040 align:middle line:84%
who went through what
he went through out

00:11:54.040 --> 00:11:56.620 align:middle line:84%
of sheer, wild
love for humanity,

00:11:56.620 --> 00:11:59.670 align:middle line:90%
would not embrace everyone?

00:11:59.670 --> 00:12:04.180 align:middle line:84%
Every broken, dispossessed,
desolate, heartbroken,

00:12:04.180 --> 00:12:05.810 align:middle line:90%
shattered person?

00:12:05.810 --> 00:12:08.530 align:middle line:84%
After all, he showed
that in his life, my God.

00:12:08.530 --> 00:12:10.750 align:middle line:84%
He hung out with
thieves and prostitutes.

00:12:10.750 --> 00:12:12.724 align:middle line:90%
He wasn't into the holy rollers.

00:12:12.724 --> 00:12:15.140 align:middle line:84%
And one of my favorite things,
one of my favorite stories,

00:12:15.140 --> 00:12:18.280 align:middle line:84%
is how he announced his
messiah-ship, his mission,

00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:22.680 align:middle line:84%
his divine purpose by the
well of Jacob to a woman

00:12:22.680 --> 00:12:26.980 align:middle line:84%
who had been divorced five
times, was a Sumerian.

00:12:26.980 --> 00:12:29.310 align:middle line:84%
So doubly outcast,
doubly rejected.

00:12:29.310 --> 00:12:30.700 align:middle line:90%
And, of course, a woman.

00:12:30.700 --> 00:12:33.370 align:middle line:84%
So not to some
guy in a robe, but

00:12:33.370 --> 00:12:35.620 align:middle line:84%
to a woman who was
considered disgusting,

00:12:35.620 --> 00:12:39.320 align:middle line:84%
he announced the great
secret of why he'd come.

00:12:39.320 --> 00:12:43.170 align:middle line:84%
So he's saying, through all
of these different ways,

00:12:43.170 --> 00:12:44.790 align:middle line:90%
I love everyone.

00:12:44.790 --> 00:12:47.140 align:middle line:84%
Everyone is welcome
to the feast.

00:12:47.140 --> 00:12:50.720 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter whether you
are gay, or straight, or black,

00:12:50.720 --> 00:12:52.160 align:middle line:84%
or white, or
Buddhist, or Hindu--

00:12:52.160 --> 00:12:53.410 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Divorced five times.

00:12:53.410 --> 00:12:56.150 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: --or a lesbian
go-go dancer in Caracas.

00:12:56.150 --> 00:12:58.340 align:middle line:84%
You are my brother
and my sister.

00:12:58.340 --> 00:13:01.840 align:middle line:84%
And I came to show you
that you're divine.

00:13:01.840 --> 00:13:05.345 align:middle line:84%
And you can become divine
if you surrender your love

00:13:05.345 --> 00:13:07.750 align:middle line:90%
to God and your life to God.

00:13:07.750 --> 00:13:11.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this had to
have an innate understanding.

00:13:11.280 --> 00:13:13.930 align:middle line:84%
And now this is a little going
more toward the science of it,

00:13:13.930 --> 00:13:17.750 align:middle line:84%
but an innate understanding
of the multi-dimensionality

00:13:17.750 --> 00:13:20.720 align:middle line:84%
of what it is to be human,
which we still don't truly

00:13:20.720 --> 00:13:22.190 align:middle line:90%
understand to this day.

00:13:22.190 --> 00:13:24.330 align:middle line:84%
Only maybe a handful
of people on the planet

00:13:24.330 --> 00:13:28.570 align:middle line:84%
know what it is to truly merge
with their other part that

00:13:28.570 --> 00:13:31.250 align:middle line:84%
is of a non-physical
and permanent nature.

00:13:31.250 --> 00:13:33.960 align:middle line:84%
And so he obviously understood
these deep principles

00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:36.360 align:middle line:84%
and was simply
trying to help people

00:13:36.360 --> 00:13:39.490 align:middle line:90%
remember that aspect of self.

00:13:39.490 --> 00:13:42.470 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Well, everyone
is the divine in drag.

00:13:42.470 --> 00:13:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And everyone is the divine
enacting a certain role, which

00:13:47.510 --> 00:13:50.780 align:middle line:84%
is crucial for the
future of the planet.

00:13:50.780 --> 00:13:53.330 align:middle line:84%
Everyone needs to turn
up as their fullest,

00:13:53.330 --> 00:13:58.830 align:middle line:84%
divine human self in order
for the plan to be successful.

00:13:58.830 --> 00:14:00.310 align:middle line:90%
It's like a piece of music.

00:14:00.310 --> 00:14:04.670 align:middle line:84%
Every note in a Mozart symphony
is absolutely essential.

00:14:04.670 --> 00:14:07.290 align:middle line:84%
And without that
note being sounded,

00:14:07.290 --> 00:14:09.320 align:middle line:90%
the symphony falls apart.

00:14:09.320 --> 00:14:13.650 align:middle line:84%
So the whole purpose of life is
to realize that you are divine.

00:14:13.650 --> 00:14:15.251 align:middle line:90%
And you're also human.

00:14:15.251 --> 00:14:17.500 align:middle line:84%
You're also the divine
appearing in this material body

00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:18.584 align:middle line:90%
with a mission of justice.

00:14:18.584 --> 00:14:20.041 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're an
unusual species.

00:14:20.041 --> 00:14:21.916 align:middle line:84%
We're a very unusual
species in that respect.

00:14:21.916 --> 00:14:22.499 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Yes.

00:14:22.499 --> 00:14:24.300 align:middle line:84%
And that's why we're
so screwed up also,

00:14:24.300 --> 00:14:25.760 align:middle line:84%
because it's very
difficult to be

00:14:25.760 --> 00:14:27.260 align:middle line:90%
these two things in the same.

00:14:27.260 --> 00:14:28.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The
duality is really--

00:14:28.850 --> 00:14:31.551 align:middle line:84%
I don't know that the universe
has duality like this anywhere

00:14:31.551 --> 00:14:32.050 align:middle line:90%
else.

00:14:32.050 --> 00:14:32.680 align:middle line:90%
This is really incredible.

00:14:32.680 --> 00:14:34.304 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Well it's
not really duality.

00:14:34.304 --> 00:14:38.140 align:middle line:84%
It is because God is both
formless and appearing in form.

00:14:38.140 --> 00:14:41.300 align:middle line:84%
It's actually non-dual
because, as the Buddha said,

00:14:41.300 --> 00:14:42.967 align:middle line:84%
form is emptiness and
emptiness is form.

00:14:42.967 --> 00:14:43.925 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That is true.

00:14:43.925 --> 00:14:46.050 align:middle line:84%
It's showing it's polarities
of one and the same.

00:14:46.050 --> 00:14:46.390 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Exactly.

00:14:46.390 --> 00:14:47.056 align:middle line:90%
It's polarities.

00:14:47.056 --> 00:14:50.340 align:middle line:84%
Because God is the opposition,
the marriage of opposites.

00:14:50.340 --> 00:14:53.040 align:middle line:84%
And what we are is that
same marriage of opposites,

00:14:53.040 --> 00:14:54.660 align:middle line:90%
both transcendent and imminent.

00:14:54.660 --> 00:14:56.620 align:middle line:90%
Both spirit and matter.

00:14:56.620 --> 00:14:59.050 align:middle line:84%
And they fuse in
a mystery which is

00:14:59.050 --> 00:15:00.850 align:middle line:90%
the source of our true identity.

00:15:00.850 --> 00:15:02.839 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And yet,
we're taught things

00:15:02.839 --> 00:15:04.630 align:middle line:84%
such as what I was
taught in Sunday school.

00:15:04.630 --> 00:15:05.760 align:middle line:90%
And the way I was raised.

00:15:05.760 --> 00:15:06.650 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Well
they teach you that

00:15:06.650 --> 00:15:08.140 align:middle line:84%
stuff because they
want to control you.

00:15:08.140 --> 00:15:09.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well and
we're going to get

00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:11.020 align:middle line:84%
into the control
in just a second.

00:15:11.020 --> 00:15:14.520 align:middle line:84%
But what happens is
it has thrust millions

00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:17.920 align:middle line:84%
upon millions of people
that were under-- that

00:15:17.920 --> 00:15:20.910 align:middle line:84%
were in one Christian
faith or another into India

00:15:20.910 --> 00:15:24.285 align:middle line:84%
and across the borders of Tibet
to try to find the answers.

00:15:24.285 --> 00:15:26.020 align:middle line:84%
And tell me from
your perspective,

00:15:26.020 --> 00:15:27.900 align:middle line:84%
because you're so
well steeped in both

00:15:27.900 --> 00:15:30.937 align:middle line:84%
of these other religions, let's
just take those two for now.

00:15:30.937 --> 00:15:33.270 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, Rumi, which
we'll get to a little later.

00:15:33.270 --> 00:15:33.690 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Oh, God.

00:15:33.690 --> 00:15:34.005 align:middle line:90%
I'd love to.

00:15:34.005 --> 00:15:34.505 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:15:34.505 --> 00:15:37.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk about what
it is, in your own opinion,

00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:41.610 align:middle line:84%
that shines about this one
particular path of the Christ,

00:15:41.610 --> 00:15:46.539 align:middle line:84%
as opposed to Buddha and as
opposed to the Hindu teachings.

00:15:46.539 --> 00:15:47.330 align:middle line:90%
What is it that's--

00:15:47.330 --> 00:15:49.829 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: Well I wouldn't ever
use the word "as opposed to,"

00:15:49.829 --> 00:15:52.450 align:middle line:84%
because I think-- I'll tell
you what I really think.

00:15:52.450 --> 00:15:54.330 align:middle line:84%
And you know how
reticent and restrained

00:15:54.330 --> 00:15:56.197 align:middle line:84%
I usually am about
expressing myself,

00:15:56.197 --> 00:15:57.280 align:middle line:90%
but you're drawing me out.

00:15:57.280 --> 00:15:59.363 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Please say it
in your restrained manner.

00:15:59.363 --> 00:16:01.850 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: I think
that humanity is

00:16:01.850 --> 00:16:04.990 align:middle line:90%
on a great evolutionary journey.

00:16:04.990 --> 00:16:07.460 align:middle line:84%
And that the destiny of
this evolutionary journey

00:16:07.460 --> 00:16:14.950 align:middle line:84%
is to embody the divine on Earth
in an embodied divine humanity.

00:16:14.950 --> 00:16:18.070 align:middle line:84%
And this is immensely difficult,
and immensely glorious,

00:16:18.070 --> 00:16:19.730 align:middle line:90%
and immensely challenging.

00:16:19.730 --> 00:16:22.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the time
for this radical embodiment

00:16:22.620 --> 00:16:24.320 align:middle line:90%
of the divine has come.

00:16:24.320 --> 00:16:28.290 align:middle line:84%
And that the sign of it is
the enormous, terrible crisis.

00:16:28.290 --> 00:16:31.820 align:middle line:84%
Evolution proceeds
by compulsive crises.

00:16:31.820 --> 00:16:34.450 align:middle line:84%
And I think if you
step back and look

00:16:34.450 --> 00:16:37.275 align:middle line:84%
at the evolutionary
history of the human race,

00:16:37.275 --> 00:16:42.360 align:middle line:84%
you see that we emerged
from the animals,

00:16:42.360 --> 00:16:48.460 align:middle line:84%
we created a gorgeous, shamanic,
matriarchal culture embedded

00:16:48.460 --> 00:16:53.010 align:middle line:84%
in the radiance of nature, which
was a very important foundation

00:16:53.010 --> 00:16:56.340 align:middle line:84%
and remains an essential
foundation for wisdom.

00:16:56.340 --> 00:16:59.820 align:middle line:84%
Then in the sixth and
seventh centuries BC,

00:16:59.820 --> 00:17:01.940 align:middle line:84%
there was what we
call the First Axial

00:17:01.940 --> 00:17:05.829 align:middle line:84%
Age in which a major
breakthrough, which gave us

00:17:05.829 --> 00:17:10.339 align:middle line:84%
access to a major new power and
understanding, was affected.

00:17:10.339 --> 00:17:13.470 align:middle line:84%
And it blazed in The
Upanishads in Hinduism.

00:17:13.470 --> 00:17:16.880 align:middle line:84%
It blazed softly in the
sublime life of the Buddha.

00:17:16.880 --> 00:17:19.950 align:middle line:84%
It blazed in Confucius'
brilliant understanding

00:17:19.950 --> 00:17:23.582 align:middle line:84%
of the relationship of
the spirit and society.

00:17:23.582 --> 00:17:24.990 align:middle line:90%
It burned in Lao Tzu.

00:17:24.990 --> 00:17:28.780 align:middle line:84%
It was a huge breakthrough
into the transcendent,

00:17:28.780 --> 00:17:32.960 align:middle line:84%
into the infinite
light that is actually

00:17:32.960 --> 00:17:35.030 align:middle line:90%
our deep, secret origin.

00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:37.550 align:middle line:90%
However, there was one problem.

00:17:37.550 --> 00:17:39.230 align:middle line:84%
And that was that
this breakthrough

00:17:39.230 --> 00:17:42.900 align:middle line:84%
was so gob-smacking,
so shattering,

00:17:42.900 --> 00:17:46.250 align:middle line:84%
that it actually set up a
kind of secret addiction.

00:17:46.250 --> 00:17:50.430 align:middle line:84%
Those traditions became addicted
to the transcendent, addicted

00:17:50.430 --> 00:17:52.060 align:middle line:90%
to the infinite light.

00:17:52.060 --> 00:17:56.110 align:middle line:84%
And they were so amazed by it
and so devastated and shattered

00:17:56.110 --> 00:17:58.940 align:middle line:84%
by its revelation that
they privileged it

00:17:58.940 --> 00:18:03.946 align:middle line:84%
as the unique goal, missing
the subtle interplay

00:18:03.946 --> 00:18:05.945 align:middle line:84%
between the light and
matter, between the father

00:18:05.945 --> 00:18:10.720 align:middle line:84%
and the mother, between this
great source and the creations

00:18:10.720 --> 00:18:12.799 align:middle line:84%
of the source, which
are just as holy.

00:18:12.799 --> 00:18:14.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So it was
bypassing, essentially,

00:18:14.590 --> 00:18:15.564 align:middle line:90%
our material aspect?

00:18:15.564 --> 00:18:16.480 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Well it was.

00:18:16.480 --> 00:18:19.990 align:middle line:84%
And what happened was that it
created a subtle dissociation,

00:18:19.990 --> 00:18:23.050 align:middle line:84%
a subtle schizophrenia between
masculine and feminine,

00:18:23.050 --> 00:18:26.890 align:middle line:84%
between creator and creation,
between human and divine,

00:18:26.890 --> 00:18:30.250 align:middle line:84%
and between society
and the enlightened.

00:18:30.250 --> 00:18:33.170 align:middle line:90%
And this was very dangerous.

00:18:33.170 --> 00:18:36.010 align:middle line:90%
Then he came.

00:18:36.010 --> 00:18:42.750 align:middle line:84%
Jesus came, not to abandon the
past, but to sum up the pie.

00:18:42.750 --> 00:18:45.640 align:middle line:84%
In a way, he began
where the others ended.

00:18:45.640 --> 00:18:48.120 align:middle line:84%
He began with this tremendous,
shamanic background.

00:18:48.120 --> 00:18:49.900 align:middle line:90%
He was a shaman, Jesus.

00:18:49.900 --> 00:18:52.320 align:middle line:90%
The donkey, he rode on a donkey.

00:18:52.320 --> 00:18:54.620 align:middle line:84%
He had shamanic
powers of healing.

00:18:54.620 --> 00:18:55.610 align:middle line:90%
All of that.

00:18:55.610 --> 00:18:59.190 align:middle line:84%
He was also absolutely grounded
in the transcendent origin

00:18:59.190 --> 00:19:01.720 align:middle line:84%
of the Upanishads, and
Lao Tzu, and Buddha.

00:19:01.720 --> 00:19:07.690 align:middle line:84%
But he was also the son
of the divine mother,

00:19:07.690 --> 00:19:09.290 align:middle line:90%
the motherhood of God.

00:19:09.290 --> 00:19:11.920 align:middle line:84%
And he had the passion of
the mother for reality.

00:19:11.920 --> 00:19:15.460 align:middle line:84%
And he had the sense,
the deep understanding,

00:19:15.460 --> 00:19:17.736 align:middle line:84%
that the mother gives
of the utter sacredness

00:19:17.736 --> 00:19:18.860 align:middle line:90%
and holiness of everything.

00:19:18.860 --> 00:19:20.425 align:middle line:84%
Of this flower,
of our connection,

00:19:20.425 --> 00:19:24.230 align:middle line:84%
of our connection
as we're talking.

00:19:24.230 --> 00:19:28.910 align:middle line:84%
This interconnected, radiant
web of sacred reality.

00:19:28.910 --> 00:19:33.630 align:middle line:84%
And what Jesus brought in is
essential for the human race.

00:19:33.630 --> 00:19:34.920 align:middle line:90%
Not just for Christians.

00:19:34.920 --> 00:19:39.650 align:middle line:84%
He brought in a vision
of God as burning,

00:19:39.650 --> 00:19:44.280 align:middle line:84%
passionate, compassionate,
personal love,

00:19:44.280 --> 00:19:48.870 align:middle line:84%
as well as impersonal
grandeur and realization.

00:19:48.870 --> 00:19:50.740 align:middle line:90%
Again, a marriage of opposites.

00:19:50.740 --> 00:19:55.219 align:middle line:84%
And he brought in what his
own tradition had taught him

00:19:55.219 --> 00:19:57.260 align:middle line:84%
through the great prophets
and through the wisdom

00:19:57.260 --> 00:20:00.170 align:middle line:84%
tradition of the great
Jewish revelation.

00:20:00.170 --> 00:20:04.990 align:middle line:84%
He brought in the knowledge
that this love is in us

00:20:04.990 --> 00:20:10.160 align:middle line:84%
to help us co-create with
God the kingdom, queendom,

00:20:10.160 --> 00:20:12.040 align:middle line:90%
on Earth.

00:20:12.040 --> 00:20:16.520 align:middle line:84%
A wholly new way of being
and doing everything.

00:20:16.520 --> 00:20:19.380 align:middle line:84%
So this was an
evolutionary breakthrough.

00:20:19.380 --> 00:20:22.830 align:middle line:84%
And if you see the progress
of the religions like this,

00:20:22.830 --> 00:20:25.830 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't mean that you
don't revere the Upanishads.

00:20:25.830 --> 00:20:29.670 align:middle line:84%
I am lost in awe before
the grandeur of the Hindu

00:20:29.670 --> 00:20:30.890 align:middle line:90%
tradition.

00:20:30.890 --> 00:20:33.480 align:middle line:84%
The Buddhist tradition is
something that I've plunged in.

00:20:33.480 --> 00:20:35.890 align:middle line:84%
I co-wrote with Patrick
Gaffney, "The Tibetan Book

00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:36.920 align:middle line:90%
of Living and Dying."

00:20:36.920 --> 00:20:40.310 align:middle line:84%
I have a very deep reverence for
his holiness, the Dalai Lama.

00:20:40.310 --> 00:20:42.070 align:middle line:84%
I've studied very
deeply in Buddhism.

00:20:42.070 --> 00:20:44.870 align:middle line:84%
And I honor the ideal
of the bodhisattva.

00:20:44.870 --> 00:20:48.780 align:middle line:84%
But there's a difference
between enlightened compassion

00:20:48.780 --> 00:20:50.750 align:middle line:90%
and burning love.

00:20:50.750 --> 00:20:56.110 align:middle line:84%
And Jesus is the
avatar, or the apostle,

00:20:56.110 --> 00:20:59.780 align:middle line:84%
or the instrument of this
revelation of burning love.

00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And I feel that our
movement on the planet now,

00:21:05.040 --> 00:21:08.900 align:middle line:84%
our evolutionary movement,
could be so transformed

00:21:08.900 --> 00:21:13.000 align:middle line:84%
if people could connect
beyond religion, beyond dogma,

00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:17.920 align:middle line:84%
to this passionate, fiery,
burning love for reality.

00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:20.960 align:middle line:84%
Because that would connect
a spiritual realization

00:21:20.960 --> 00:21:23.530 align:middle line:84%
with sacred action
and make of us

00:21:23.530 --> 00:21:26.780 align:middle line:84%
all humble revolutionaries
of love in action.

00:21:26.780 --> 00:21:28.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I think
Jesus has created.

00:21:28.530 --> 00:21:30.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I can't imagine anyone
saying it more beautifully

00:21:30.390 --> 00:21:31.370 align:middle line:90%
than what you've just said.

00:21:31.370 --> 00:21:31.850 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Thank you, darling.

00:21:31.850 --> 00:21:34.223 align:middle line:84%
So there's no opposition to
any of the other traditions.

00:21:34.223 --> 00:21:36.400 align:middle line:90%
It's a completion in a way.

00:21:36.400 --> 00:21:39.000 align:middle line:84%
It's look at one image of
it-- sorry to go on you,

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:40.850 align:middle line:84%
but you've raised a
kind of radiant worm.

00:21:40.850 --> 00:21:41.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No, please do.

00:21:41.850 --> 00:21:46.070 align:middle line:84%
>>HARVEY: It's as if what the
great Hindu, and Buddhist,

00:21:46.070 --> 00:21:50.520 align:middle line:84%
and Daoist revelations did
was to awaken the light

00:21:50.520 --> 00:21:52.630 align:middle line:90%
and to reveal the light in us.

00:21:52.630 --> 00:21:58.700 align:middle line:84%
But what Jesus was was a lens,
a lens through which the light

00:21:58.700 --> 00:22:04.690 align:middle line:84%
can become focused on real
problems in the real world.

00:22:04.690 --> 00:22:07.300 align:middle line:84%
On poverty, on injustice,
on the horrible treatment

00:22:07.300 --> 00:22:08.210 align:middle line:90%
of gay people.

00:22:08.210 --> 00:22:09.918 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which was
part of his activism.

00:22:09.918 --> 00:22:12.030 align:middle line:90%


00:22:12.030 --> 00:22:14.217 align:middle line:84%
Historically, it was
part of his activism.

00:22:14.217 --> 00:22:14.800 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Yes.

00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:17.506 align:middle line:84%
He's the most radical person
that's ever been on the Earth.

00:22:17.506 --> 00:22:21.010 align:middle line:84%
He absolutely un-wrote
the patriarchy

00:22:21.010 --> 00:22:23.280 align:middle line:84%
before the patriarchy
really blazed into being.

00:22:23.280 --> 00:22:25.576 align:middle line:84%
He came at the moment
when the Romans

00:22:25.576 --> 00:22:26.950 align:middle line:84%
were going to take
over the world

00:22:26.950 --> 00:22:30.190 align:middle line:84%
and make the patriarchal way
of being the only way of being

00:22:30.190 --> 00:22:31.940 align:middle line:84%
and then risk the
psychosis, which

00:22:31.940 --> 00:22:33.420 align:middle line:90%
is now threatening the world.

00:22:33.420 --> 00:22:36.150 align:middle line:84%
And he came as a man, not
because men are superior,

00:22:36.150 --> 00:22:38.070 align:middle line:84%
but because men were
about to go crazy

00:22:38.070 --> 00:22:40.720 align:middle line:84%
with this obscene
vision of power.

00:22:40.720 --> 00:22:42.860 align:middle line:84%
And he showed the
exact opposite way.

00:22:42.860 --> 00:22:45.450 align:middle line:84%
He showed the way
through, the way out.

00:22:45.450 --> 00:22:49.480 align:middle line:84%
And the way out was through
surrender, and humility,

00:22:49.480 --> 00:22:54.710 align:middle line:84%
and love, and tenderness,
and a passion for justice.

00:22:54.710 --> 00:22:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And a real, radical respect
for all forms of life.

00:22:59.550 --> 00:23:01.290 align:middle line:84%
It could not be a
more important message

00:23:01.290 --> 00:23:02.870 align:middle line:84%
for the whole world
at this moment.

00:23:02.870 --> 00:23:05.314 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Too bad
it didn't take.

00:23:05.314 --> 00:23:06.230 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: It did take.

00:23:06.230 --> 00:23:07.750 align:middle line:84%
It didn't take in the
churches, because they all

00:23:07.750 --> 00:23:09.540 align:middle line:84%
got taken over by
the boy's club.

00:23:09.540 --> 00:23:12.100 align:middle line:84%
And the great catastrophe
was when the Roman Empire

00:23:12.100 --> 00:23:14.825 align:middle line:84%
made Christianity its
official religion.

00:23:14.825 --> 00:23:16.450 align:middle line:84%
And there were many
other catastrophes.

00:23:16.450 --> 00:23:20.160 align:middle line:84%
Then we have the farce of the
Vatican and all the rest of it.

00:23:20.160 --> 00:23:24.930 align:middle line:84%
But it took in some of
the extraordinary mystics.

00:23:24.930 --> 00:23:27.990 align:middle line:84%
And Christianity actually, the
Christian mystical tradition,

00:23:27.990 --> 00:23:30.160 align:middle line:84%
is as glorious as
any of the others.

00:23:30.160 --> 00:23:31.910 align:middle line:84%
And what I'd love to
say to all seekers

00:23:31.910 --> 00:23:34.752 align:middle line:84%
out there who may have
absolutely turned away

00:23:34.752 --> 00:23:36.710 align:middle line:84%
from Jesus because of
the horrible image of him

00:23:36.710 --> 00:23:41.180 align:middle line:84%
as a misogynistic,
homophobic tyrant claiming

00:23:41.180 --> 00:23:43.280 align:middle line:84%
total uniqueness--
all that nonsense

00:23:43.280 --> 00:23:45.350 align:middle line:84%
that we've been sold
by the boy's club who

00:23:45.350 --> 00:23:49.170 align:middle line:84%
want to control us through
that image-- get rid of that,

00:23:49.170 --> 00:23:53.300 align:middle line:84%
and listen to the
amazing message.

00:23:53.300 --> 00:23:55.220 align:middle line:84%
And plunge into the
great Christian mystics.

00:23:55.220 --> 00:23:57.790 align:middle line:84%
Because if you do,
you'll find that you

00:23:57.790 --> 00:24:01.390 align:middle line:84%
will find an extraordinary
range of understanding.

00:24:01.390 --> 00:24:04.455 align:middle line:84%
Look at Theresa of Avila, one of
the greatest mystics who's ever

00:24:04.455 --> 00:24:06.390 align:middle line:84%
been here, who has a
deeper understanding

00:24:06.390 --> 00:24:08.330 align:middle line:84%
of the interior
life than anybody.

00:24:08.330 --> 00:24:11.720 align:middle line:84%
Look at Radovich of
Antwerp, one of my craziest

00:24:11.720 --> 00:24:14.320 align:middle line:84%
and most magnificent
friends of the soul.

00:24:14.320 --> 00:24:18.090 align:middle line:84%
She was this burning, Rumi-like
poet of the twelfth century.

00:24:18.090 --> 00:24:19.940 align:middle line:90%
Mad for love of God.

00:24:19.940 --> 00:24:22.370 align:middle line:84%
Look at Matilda of Magdeburg,
the incredible woman who

00:24:22.370 --> 00:24:25.090 align:middle line:84%
understood that Jesus was a
mother as well as a father.

00:24:25.090 --> 00:24:28.590 align:middle line:84%
Look at Julian of Norwich,
look at Meister Eckhart,

00:24:28.590 --> 00:24:30.310 align:middle line:90%
look at Rickebrick.

00:24:30.310 --> 00:24:33.160 align:middle line:84%
Look, in our time, at people
like Howard Thurman, who

00:24:33.160 --> 00:24:35.660 align:middle line:84%
wrote that book that
Martin Luther King carried

00:24:35.660 --> 00:24:38.270 align:middle line:84%
into jail with him, "Jesus
and The Disinherited."

00:24:38.270 --> 00:24:42.660 align:middle line:84%
Look at Matthew Fox doing this
staggering, monumental work,

00:24:42.660 --> 00:24:46.080 align:middle line:84%
bringing in the whole
vision of the cosmic Christ,

00:24:46.080 --> 00:24:48.440 align:middle line:84%
the whole universe lit
up with the glory of God.

00:24:48.440 --> 00:24:51.290 align:middle line:84%
Look at the Celtic
mystics, who worshipped

00:24:51.290 --> 00:24:53.970 align:middle line:84%
Jesus in every flower,
in every rabbit,

00:24:53.970 --> 00:24:57.190 align:middle line:84%
and in the vision of the
whole creation as singing

00:24:57.190 --> 00:24:58.610 align:middle line:90%
the praises of God.

00:24:58.610 --> 00:25:01.440 align:middle line:84%
And when you do come into the
Christian mystical tradition

00:25:01.440 --> 00:25:04.830 align:middle line:84%
like this, you see that it
is just as powerful, just as

00:25:04.830 --> 00:25:06.710 align:middle line:84%
noble, just as
grand as any other.

00:25:06.710 --> 00:25:11.070 align:middle line:84%
And gifted, at its core, with
this particular understanding

00:25:11.070 --> 00:25:14.170 align:middle line:84%
of passionate love for
justice and compassion,

00:25:14.170 --> 00:25:15.740 align:middle line:90%
which is so important.

00:25:15.740 --> 00:25:19.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you can't go
there without addressing

00:25:19.370 --> 00:25:21.720 align:middle line:84%
the divinity in the
feminine, of course,

00:25:21.720 --> 00:25:23.500 align:middle line:90%
which is the other part of this.

00:25:23.500 --> 00:25:24.609 align:middle line:90%
And so what happened?

00:25:24.609 --> 00:25:25.150 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: Mm.

00:25:25.150 --> 00:25:26.457 align:middle line:90%
That's a lovely one.

00:25:26.457 --> 00:25:27.040 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:25:27.040 --> 00:25:34.130 align:middle line:84%
And why was mother Mary elevated
while Mary Magdalene was

00:25:34.130 --> 00:25:35.010 align:middle line:90%
cast aside?

00:25:35.010 --> 00:25:38.950 align:middle line:10%
>>HARVEY: Well let's look at
it-- let's start with Jesus.

00:25:38.950 --> 00:25:41.170 align:middle line:10%
I want to tell you
one of the greatest

00:25:41.170 --> 00:25:42.580 align:middle line:10%
experiences of my life.

00:25:42.580 --> 00:25:44.740 align:middle line:10%
I've been to Israel three times.

00:25:44.740 --> 00:25:48.400 align:middle line:10%
And I've been in the
places where he was.

00:25:48.400 --> 00:25:49.550 align:middle line:90%
And is.

00:25:49.550 --> 00:25:53.750 align:middle line:84%
And when, on my first
visit, I went to Tabgha,

00:25:53.750 --> 00:25:55.770 align:middle line:84%
which is where he
gave the Beatitudes.

00:25:55.770 --> 00:26:00.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's a rolling, gorgeous
meadow filled with wild flowers

00:26:00.500 --> 00:26:01.560 align:middle line:90%
by the sea of Galilee.

00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:05.360 align:middle line:84%
And I stood in this
field of wild flowers

00:26:05.360 --> 00:26:07.770 align:middle line:84%
which was saturated by
soft, spring sunlight.

00:26:07.770 --> 00:26:10.205 align:middle line:84%
And I gazed across
the glittering blue

00:26:10.205 --> 00:26:11.780 align:middle line:90%
of the sea of Galilee.

00:26:11.780 --> 00:26:14.990 align:middle line:84%
And saw the soft-breasted
hills around it.

00:26:14.990 --> 00:26:21.190 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly it burst upon me
that everything that he ever

00:26:21.190 --> 00:26:25.220 align:middle line:84%
championed, the Beatitudes--
"Blessed are the pure in heart,

00:26:25.220 --> 00:26:26.500 align:middle line:90%
for they shall see God.

00:26:26.500 --> 00:26:29.760 align:middle line:84%
Blessed are those who mourn,
for they shall be comforted"--

00:26:29.760 --> 00:26:33.130 align:middle line:90%
it's all Mother transmission.

00:26:33.130 --> 00:26:37.450 align:middle line:84%
He was as much a son of the
mother, a child of the mother,

00:26:37.450 --> 00:26:40.380 align:middle line:84%
as he was of the
transcendent father.

00:26:40.380 --> 00:26:43.950 align:middle line:84%
And when you see
that, when you really

00:26:43.950 --> 00:26:47.510 align:middle line:84%
know that Jesus was a
sacred androgen, someone

00:26:47.510 --> 00:26:50.030 align:middle line:84%
fusing at the
greatest and deepest

00:26:50.030 --> 00:26:54.710 align:middle line:84%
depths, the transcendent piece
of the Father with the burning,

00:26:54.710 --> 00:27:00.090 align:middle line:84%
compassionate passion of
all the truth of the Mother,

00:27:00.090 --> 00:27:02.020 align:middle line:84%
then you understand that
what he's bringing in

00:27:02.020 --> 00:27:04.610 align:middle line:90%
is the true sacred marriage.

00:27:04.610 --> 00:27:08.860 align:middle line:84%
And he's representing the
empowered, humble, loving life

00:27:08.860 --> 00:27:10.710 align:middle line:90%
that that gives birth to.

00:27:10.710 --> 00:27:13.800 align:middle line:84%
And then you look at
actually how he lived.

00:27:13.800 --> 00:27:16.140 align:middle line:90%
He didn't live as a guru.

00:27:16.140 --> 00:27:19.380 align:middle line:84%
He lived as a traveling
troubadour of God.

00:27:19.380 --> 00:27:23.370 align:middle line:90%
He always said, don't love me.

00:27:23.370 --> 00:27:24.640 align:middle line:90%
Don't idolize me.

00:27:24.640 --> 00:27:27.250 align:middle line:84%
It's your faith
that has healed you.

00:27:27.250 --> 00:27:30.890 align:middle line:84%
He got dressed up as a female
servant at the Last Supper

00:27:30.890 --> 00:27:31.920 align:middle line:90%
and washed their feet.

00:27:31.920 --> 00:27:34.550 align:middle line:90%
And said, don't project on me.

00:27:34.550 --> 00:27:35.810 align:middle line:90%
Stop it.

00:27:35.810 --> 00:27:39.650 align:middle line:90%
You must be me in action.

00:27:39.650 --> 00:27:42.360 align:middle line:84%
And look at the relationships
that he had with women.

00:27:42.360 --> 00:27:46.620 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't simply that he
had an enlightened mother.

00:27:46.620 --> 00:27:50.080 align:middle line:84%
And Mary is the divine
mother, the embodied mother.

00:27:50.080 --> 00:27:51.110 align:middle line:90%
They came together.

00:27:51.110 --> 00:27:54.170 align:middle line:84%
It's a mother,
son, father dance.

00:27:54.170 --> 00:27:58.820 align:middle line:84%
But he had a consort,
probably a tantric consort,

00:27:58.820 --> 00:28:00.440 align:middle line:90%
in Mary Magdalene.

00:28:00.440 --> 00:28:03.230 align:middle line:84%
Someone whom he
adored, and who adored

00:28:03.230 --> 00:28:05.400 align:middle line:84%
him, was present
at the crucifixion,

00:28:05.400 --> 00:28:09.570 align:middle line:84%
was the first person
to see him resurrected.

00:28:09.570 --> 00:28:14.350 align:middle line:84%
She was almost totally written
out of the later tradition

00:28:14.350 --> 00:28:18.370 align:middle line:84%
because the boy's club
wanted to control it

00:28:18.370 --> 00:28:23.330 align:middle line:84%
and couldn't face the full,
outrageous radicalism of Jesus'

00:28:23.330 --> 00:28:27.939 align:middle line:84%
overturning of all the
previous ways of being--

00:28:27.939 --> 00:28:29.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Of his pure humanity.

00:28:29.230 --> 00:28:30.240 align:middle line:90%
Simple humanity.

00:28:30.240 --> 00:28:31.620 align:middle line:90%
>>HARVEY: His tenderness.

00:28:31.620 --> 00:28:33.300 align:middle line:90%
But his femininity.

00:28:33.300 --> 00:28:35.030 align:middle line:90%
Why do we love Jesus?

00:28:35.030 --> 00:28:39.405 align:middle line:84%
It's because he is-- of
course, he's grand, and strong,

00:28:39.405 --> 00:28:40.740 align:middle line:90%
and he does miracles.

00:28:40.740 --> 00:28:42.730 align:middle line:84%
And he's noble,
and he's powerful.

00:28:42.730 --> 00:28:45.940 align:middle line:84%
He has the full beauty of
the sacred masculine in him.

00:28:45.940 --> 00:28:49.100 align:middle line:84%
But he's also
unbelievably tender,

00:28:49.100 --> 00:28:51.890 align:middle line:90%
and shattered, and vulnerable.

00:28:51.890 --> 00:28:56.810 align:middle line:84%
And he's also outraged,
as a lioness is outraged,

00:28:56.810 --> 00:29:01.370 align:middle line:84%
as the black Madonna is outraged
by any kind of cruelty to life.

00:29:01.370 --> 00:29:03.840 align:middle line:84%
He has the mother
outrage at things.

00:29:03.840 --> 00:29:08.420 align:middle line:84%
So he brings both with
such enormous truth.

00:29:08.420 --> 00:29:12.210 align:middle line:84%
When you see that, when
you begin to comprehend it,

00:29:12.210 --> 00:29:15.560 align:middle line:84%
it changes your complete vision
of him and of the Revelation.

00:29:15.560 --> 00:29:19.370 align:middle line:84%
It's utterly insane that women
haven't been totally let in.

00:29:19.370 --> 00:29:22.180 align:middle line:84%
They were actually bishops
until the second century.

00:29:22.180 --> 00:29:23.090 align:middle line:90%
Women were bishops.

00:29:23.090 --> 00:29:25.620 align:middle line:84%
And then the boy's club took
over, and then they were--

00:29:25.620 --> 00:29:27.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's had
devastating consequences.

00:29:27.580 --> 00:29:29.410 align:middle line:84%
You were just
talking a moment ago.

00:29:29.410 --> 00:29:31.700 align:middle line:90%
